rence work written with the intention of exposing an international audience to the explosion of Polish literature and film that emerged in the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aPolish literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aPolish literaturey20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aPolish literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh  a20th.  a21st.  aPolish.  acenturies.  acontemporary.  aculture.  ahistory.  aliterature.  anew.1 aBendyk, Edwin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBilczewski, Tomasz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBill, Stanley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBolecki, Włodzimierz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorkowska, Grażyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBraun, Kazimierz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuryła, Sławomir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarpenter, Bogdana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzaplinski, Przemyslaw, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCzapliński, Przemysław, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalkowska, Janina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFilipowicz, Halina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFoeller-Pituch, Elżbieta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGasyna, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerould, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/